sections.text:
Managers and supervisors should understand the importance of applying good hygiene practices and personnel health and hygiene, in aspects such as:
• the availability of adequate hygiene facilities;
• compliance with hand washing instructions;
• exclusion from the premises of food handlers or any persons, including children, with symptoms of gastroenteritis or acute hepatitis or those recovering from these infections (see Section 7.2);
• how to clean and disinfect surfaces when contaminated.

